Funny Not Funny!
Friends 
This kind of stuff happens!!! But worse!
There are many "Influencers" handing out Medical advise and protocols for "cleanses" that have no idea what they are doing!
Just because some healthy person can do a liver cleanse or parasite cleanse, doesn't mean someone else with an autoimmune condition is ready for it or for that same Dose!!!
⭐️ Research ingredients before purchasing a product to make sure you don't have any allergies or known reactions 
⭐️ Start low dose (micro dose) take a tiny dose of a supplement on its own before starting a full protocol before adding the next
⭐️ If your body reacts, take a break and take a micro dose a few days later to see if it was just too strong or if you actually have an allergy to an ingredient 
⭐️ Don't push to hard, there is nothing wrong with low and slow
⭐️ Journal reactions and how you feel- Sometimes we start new products and don't realize they are causing more problems unless we look back and see when it all started.
⭐️ Don't play the blame game- You never know what uour body can tolerate, You are responsible for taking things slow if you know your reactive. Always error on the side of caution.
⭐️ Just because one product is miracle for someone else, doesn't mean it will be for you. You may need work on a different root cause.

⭐️ Don't throw it out right away, Your body may just not be ready. Work on some other things and revisit. I've had products and therapies make me feel terrible one month and amazing the next 🙌
⭐️ Pray and trust your intuition. God knows best for your body, always playing a guessing game is never a good result. Make a list, pray and wait........ When you feel good an excited about something, do it then.

xoxoxo

I think there is so much stress and judgement around being a parent these days.  Sometimes we forget about the simplicity in Christ.
I personally trust God with all of my heart and he says “Train up a child in the way he should go: And when he is old, he will not depart from it.”
‭‭Proverbs‬ ‭22‬:‭6‬ ‭KJV‬‬
I know my only job on this earth is to train my children up to know Jesus.
Because if they know Jesus ans his goodness they will trust Him to be their guides. I won't need to stress about every decision they will make or about their safety everywhere they go because they will have the Holy Spirit as a guide.
What I have realized as a parent is that children don't learn as we say, they learn as we do.......
So if they see me rising early and reading my scripture in the sun rise & praise Jesus with worship in my car and while I cook, then they are learning.
We can't fake it, kids can tell. My litmus test is always the fruit of the spirit 
“But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, faith,”
‭‭Galatians‬ ‭5‬:‭22‬ ‭KJV‬‬
Am I so full of Christ that his fruit are abundant for them to see? Do they know that the Spirit in me is what brings me so much joy and peace?
Do they see how much joy it brings me to do Gods will?
That is always my prayer. 
It's also actually less burden to know that I don't have to sign them up for every sport and they don't have to be perfect singers or speak five languages and play instruments. 
I just have to teach them about my reason for my Joy and Peace in this broken world we live in.
My savior who came and died and rose from the grave, to wash our sins and give us the hope of heaven and eternity.
I cried as I watched two of my kids decide that they wanted others to see their faith. That they were not ashamed to me bold and say, Hey, I love Jesus and I everyone to know it.

I'm so thankful that God is the only judge that matters when it comes to parenting and he ordained your children to you because he knows that you will love them the best.  So don't beat yourself up, no one can raise your child better than you can. He knows that and that's why he gave them to you.... #parenting @trinitychrch

Some know the roots of Dec 25 go back to Nimrod, Seniramus and Tammuz. No it was not the birth of Christ. Actually Constantine and his mother tried to merge this day with the birth of Christ to keep the Pagans and Christians "happy". The pagans would go in the forest and chop wood in the shape of an idol that they would worship. They would adorn it with precious metals and jewels. They would often do evil sacrifices to these idols because they believed they had power. Many people in the world who celebrate Christmas do not do so because they have a relationship with Christ. They do it because it's #fun or #createsmemories or because it's a family #tradition 
What it comes down to for the believer is, Are you worshiping Jesus or not. If you have a relationship with Jesus and decide to celebrate him in December and it is not a stumbling block for your faith. You have that freedom! Congratulations 🎉 

I certainly don't go around judging salvation of others or shaming them for having a fake tree in their home and singing about their savior all month.

What we really should be watching for is the day they tell us we can't.
